    <subfield code="y">00000 Pion-mass dependence of the nucleon mass from $N_f=2$ fits. We show B$\chi$PT $p^4$ fits without (left) and with (right) explicit $\Delta(1223)$ degrees of freedom. The green-dotted lines correspond to fits to nucleon mass data alone and the blue-solid lines to simultaneous fits including also the $\sigma_{\pi N}(290)$ QCDSF data point. The lQCD data points are scaled by our $r_0 \approx 0.490$ fm obtained in the fits with $\Delta(1232)$.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1280204/files/fig_6.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00001 Left: Pion-mass dependence of the $\sigma_{\pi N}$ term from $N_f=2$ fits. The blue-solid (green-dotted) line corresponds to the B$\chi$PT $p^4$ fit with(out) the $\Delta(1232)$ with including the $\sigma_{\pi N}(290)$ data point (red-diamond). The red-square is our predicted $\sigma_{\pi N}$ value at the physical point. Right: Comparison of B$\chi$PT $p^4$ fits with $\Delta(1232)$ to $N_f=2$ (red-triangles) and $N_f=2+1$ (blue-squares) lQCD data. The blue-circle is the physical nucleon mass.</subfield>
